LAGOS- Security operatives, including uniformed policemen have laid siege to the residence of Seun Kuti, in a move to arrest him. According to a statement from the Movement of the People (MOP), an emerging political group being championed by Seun Kuti, the security siege started on Friday morning when there was an attempt to arrest him. The statement issued by the MOP Media Office and confirmed by Comrade Olaseni Ajai, a Co-convener of the group, when the security operatives stormed Seun Kuti’s residence in Ikeja, he was not around as he had left early for a radio programme. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Ajai disclosed that the policemen however took away a member of Seun Kuti’s household, and continued the siege to the area in an attempt to arrest him. Ajai, who spoke DAILY INDEPENDENT on Sunday morning, disclosed that Seun Kuti since that Friday morning had not been seen while his whereabouts remained unknown. FG Imposes Partial Lockdown Nationwide Despite Ongoing Insurance Recapitalisation, Investors Seek Return To Risk-Based Capital Model He stated that Seun Kuti, a scion of the legendary Ransome Kuti family and a son of the late Afrobeat King, Fela Anikulapo-Kuti, is the founder of the Nigerian Resistance Movement (NRM) and Co-Convener of the MOP, which had been mobilising Nigerian activists and youths for future political leadership as the nation marches towards the 2023 general elections. He stated that since the #EndSARS protest, security men had places Seun Kuti under security watch and had made several attempts to arrest himAccording to him, the security men believe that Seun Kuti, also an Afrobeat star and political activist, was one of the promoters of the #EndSARS Movement and had been doing everything possible to silence him. Ajai maintained that Seun Kuti and his friends in the NRM and MOP would not be silenced or intimidated to stop the emancipation and liberation of the Nigerian masses and the youths, who he said were being mobilised for the future leadership of the country. Ajai stressed that the journey for the liberation of the Nigerian people from tyranny of the oppressors had started and could not be stopped by the government despite all intimidation of vocal youths like Seun Kuti. He called on well meaning Nigerians, the human rights community, the Nigerian Bar Association (NBA) to call the government and security agencies to order and stop the intimidation of peaceful people and allow free speech. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION